# Copy to .env.local for local dev. These are PUBLIC (anon) values — safe in the
# browser. Find them at: Supabase dashboard → (your project) → Settings → API.
#
# TWO-TIER SETUP (free tier) — each tier has its OWN Supabase project. Point
# local dev at the DEV project; Vercel injects the right values per environment.
#
#   Tier   Git branch   Vercel env     Supabase project
#   -----  ----------   ------------   -------------------------------
#   Dev    develop      Preview        singlestack-dev          (no real data)
#   Demo   main         Production     pzulufyoqvqevjrmtmfj     (demo data)
#
# In Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables, set these two keys
# per environment: Production → the demo project, Preview → the dev project.
# Locally, fill in the DEV project's values below.
# (A Production tier can be added later — see docs/environments-setup-guide.md.)

NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-dev-project-ref.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-dev-anon-key-eyJ...
